// ==============================================================================
// extensions.json - VS Code Extension Recommendations Template
// ==============================================================================
//
// LOCATION: /.vscode/extensions.json (project root)
//
// PURPOSE:
//   Recommend and suggest VS Code extensions for team members to ensure
//   consistent development tooling. VS Code will prompt users to install
//   recommended extensions when opening the workspace.
//
// USAGE:
//   1. Create .vscode/ directory in your project root
//   2. Copy this file to .vscode/extensions.json
//   3. Uncomment extensions relevant to your project
//   4. Add project-specific extensions as needed
//
// BOOTSTRAP INTEGRATION:
//   Bootstrap scripts can customize based on omni.* config:
//   - ENABLE_PYTHON -> Include/exclude Python extensions
//   - Tech stack choices -> Relevant framework extensions
//   After setup, this file is the authoritative source for extension recommendations.
//
// ==============================================================================
